Traineeship Description:
This position reports to the Application Engineering director and interfaces with other engineering staff to support development and deployment of solutions. Traineeship includes engineering projects, tasks which will require critical thinking and relevant technical skills. The position will allow immense technical learning and gain critical soft skills such as communication, effective planning and collaboration.

Specific Responsibilities:

  Design and development of standard payload modules for the mobile robots&nbsp;
  Integration and testing of sensors and other electromechanical systems&nbsp;
  Assisting with deployment of robots at various sites&nbsp;
  Assist product development team to evaluate system limitations&nbsp;
  Electrical design and development of custom payload modules based on customer requirements

Competencies:

  Extensive hands-on learning on mobile robots and embedded systems development&nbsp;
  Strong prototyping and troubleshooting skills for mobile robots&nbsp;
  Hands-on experience with Robot Operating System (ROS)&nbsp;
  Strong programming skills in C++/Python for firmware development&nbsp;
  Understanding of multi-disciplinary project planning and management&nbsp;
  Strong understanding of robotic automation processes in the logistics and manufacturing industry

Required Educational Qualification:
Bachelor's Degree

Eligibility Criteria for SGUnited Traineeships:

  Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident; and

a.Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); or
b.Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020